South Korea Stocks: Korean Air Lines, Korea Zinc, Poongsan

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-04-13T00:37:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/south-korea-stocks-korean-air-lines-korea-zinc-poongsan.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:25 a.m. in  Seoul . The  Kospi
Index (KOSPI)  was little changed at 2,089.54.  Airlines: Korean Air Lines Co. (003490 KS), South Korea’s
largest carrier, gained 3.5 percent to 65,000 won.  Asiana
Airlines (020560)  Inc. (020560 KS) climbed 2.7 percent to 9,800 won. Oil
declined for a third day in New York.  Daewoo Engineering & Construction Co. (047040 KS), a
builder, gained 2.7 percent to 11,300 won. PT Perusahaan Listrik
Negara awarded Daewoo Engineering & Construction and its
partners a 2.5 trillion rupiah project ($289 million) to build a
60-megawatt hydro power plant in  Indonesia ’s North Sumatra
province, Dahlan Iskan, president director at Listrik Negara,
said.  Korea Zinc Co. (010130 KS), which produces gold and silver,
lost 2.2 percent to 425,500 won. Gold tumbled the most in four
weeks after a drop in energy costs reduced demand for the
precious metal as a hedge against inflation. Silver also fell.  Poongsan Corp. (103140 KS), a copper products maker,
declined 1.9 percent to 46,450 won. Copper futures for May
delivery fell 1.7 percent in  New York , the biggest loss for a
most-active contract since March 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
 sshin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
